The paper deals with the performance measurement and resource planning of computer clusters, which falls under the category of computer systems and networking (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the estimation of sojourn time, which is a common problem in queueing theory (cs.PF). The use of erasure coding based cloud storages and modern network protocols like multipath routing suggests a focus on distributed systems (cs.DC) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). Finally, the paper introduces a new linear transformation technique, which could potentially fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
